- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array `answer` is equal to the length of the integer array parameter `nums`.
- Each element in the integer array `answer` is equal to the absolute difference between the sum of elements to the left and to the right of the corresponding index in the integer array parameter `nums`.
- If there are no elements to the left of a certain index `i`, the sum is considered as 0.
- If there are no elements to the right of a certain index `i`, the sum is considered as 0.